FBIS4-6729 "dreas078_d_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-078 Daily Report 22 Apr 1994 South Korea IAEA Responds to DPRK Regarding Fuel Rods IAEA Responds to DPRK Regarding Fuel Rods SK2204005494 Seoul HANGUK ILBO in Korean 22 Apr 94 p 1 SK2204005494 Seoul HANGUK ILBO Korean BFN [Text] On the afternoon of 21 April, Hans Blix, director general of the International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA], sent a message to North Korea expressing the IAEA position on North Korea's proposal for the IAEA to witness the exchange of nuclear fuel bars at its nuclear facilities. It has been learned that Director General Blix said that the witnessing of IAEA inspectors of the exchange of nuclear fuel bars should be technically and perfectly carried out without any obstruction. He also said the inspection of the radiochemical laboratory, which was not carried out during the past inspections, should be fully resumed as well.
